fields.bio: As a DJ and avid record collector, my obsession with vinyl goes beyond the sheer enjoyment of the music. I am constantly on the hunt for new tracks and sounds to incorporate into my sets, and I collect records from different countries and genres to expand my musical repertoire. When not spinning records or organizing vinyl swap meets, I am always looking for new ways to creatively blend my collection in unique ways.

As a music historian and collector, I am driven by a deep desire to preserve the legacy of different genres and movements through vinyl records. My collection is comprised of sought-after first pressings and limited editions, and I am always on the lookout for hidden gems. When I'm not cataloging my collection or organizing listening parties, I love to research and learn more about the history behind the music.

I find great pleasure in exploring the rich sound and tactile experience of analog recordings. My collection spans across different eras and styles, and I take great pride in discovering new records to add to my collection. In my free time, I am passionate about restoring and maintaining vintage turntables.
